                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#2r #8v #16r #23v #36r #44v #55r #63r #68v #80v #92r #95r #101r #120r" facs="002 009 016 024 036 045 055 063 069 081 092 095 101 120">Fols. 2r, 8v, 16r, 23v, 36r, 44v, 55r, 63r, 68v, 80v, 92r, 95r, 101r, 120r</locus> There is a full set of colorful harags in orange, black, and yellow
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#2r #8v #16r #23v #36r #44v #55r #63r #68v #80v #92r #95r #101r #113r #120r" facs="002 009 016 024 036 045 055 063 069 081 092 095 101 113 120">Fols. 2r, 8v, 16r, 23v, 36r, 44v, 55r, 63r, 68v, 80v, 92r, 95r, 101r, 113r, 120r</locus>
                      Navigation aids: colorful strings are sewn into the fore edge of folios that mark the sections of the Psalter
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                      <title type="incomplete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Chp151">Psalms of
                                                  David, Chp151</title> contains the first two plusses that are part of the longer edition
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <desc>
                    The fourth biblical canticle is Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophet
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                    The Praises of Mary are laid out beginning with Monday and culminating in Sunday
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    <locus target="#91v #94v" facs="092 095">Fols. 91v, 94v</locus>
                    Scribal doxology, written in alternating red and black letters
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
